ilog.cplex

Interface IloCplex.AsyncHandle

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IloCplex.FeasOptHandle, IloCplex.PopulateHandle, IloCplex.RefineConflictHandle, IloCplex.RefineMIPStartConflictHandle, IloCplex.SolveFixedHandle, IloCplex.SolveHandle, IloCplex.TuneParamHandle
    Enclosing class:
    IloCplex

    public static interface IloCplex.AsyncHandle
    Handle to represent an asynchronous function call.

    • Method Detail

      • test

        boolean test()
             throws IloException

        Tests whether the operation represented by this handle is still running.

        Throws:
        IloException
        Returns:

        true if the operation represented by this handle is still running and false otherwise.

      • kill

        void kill()
          throws IloException
        Kills the operation represented by this handle.

        The semantics of "killing an operation" depend on the operation itself. You still need to join the handle by means of the method join() in order to clean any resources allocated for the handle.

        Throws:
        IloException

      • join

        void join()
          throws IloException
        Waits until the operation represented by this handle finishes.

        In other words, this method blocks until the operation either returns or is killed. The method also releases all resources allocated to this handle. Calling this method more than once on a handle raises an error.

        Throws:
        IloException
